A truck blocking the N3 as the Harrismith protest has flared up again. eNCA/Slindelo Masikane JOHANNESBURG - There seems to be no end to the violence in Harrismith as community members intensify their protest action. Residents set a truck alight on the N3 on Wednesday bringing traffic to a complete standstill. READ: Harrismith residents intensify action For weeks now community members have been demanding access to basic service delivery and to be removed from the Maluti-a-Phofung Municipality. They have promised to continue demonstrating until President Cyril Ramaphosa intervenes. Meanwhile, six people have been arrested for public violence and will appear in court on Friday.